        <section eId="sec_17a_573">
          <num>17a-573</num>
          <heading>(Formerly Sec. 17-254). When director may institute commitment proceedings</heading>
          <content>
            <p>Sec. 17a-573. (Formerly Sec. 17-254). When director may institute commitment proceedings.Within two months prior to the expiration of the maximum term of confinement authorized for any patient under section17a-567, the director of the hospital may, upon the recommendation of the board, initiate proceedings under section17a-497or17a-520for the commitment or further commitment, as the case may be, of the patient.
